column5: Hey Everyone,  Made the trek up north today... was greeted with the river i fish 90% frozen over... caught me totally off guard, small fishable area produced though. I went 3/3 with the biggest being 9lbs 2oz..enjoy         dobee
Nice fish. Those look pretty fresh too. You deserve it!!wtg.
great shots and congrats on the fish
I have some roe in the fridge...just waiting for "good" conditions to sneak out. Meanwhile I keep seeing THESE REPORTS !!!!  Beautiful photos. Good on you for getting out
Nice HAWG,...great report,..looks like one of the spots I frequent,..gonna have to get out there soon...
even the huckleberrys are gettin' 'em! LOL
Nice catch !!!! great pics too,love those fall steelhead..  well it was worth the drive wasnt it..??....cheers
Considering the conditions that's pretty impressive, congrat's!
